begin
reserve n for Nat;
reserve K for Field;
reserve M1 for (Matrix of n,K);
reserve M2 for (Matrix of n,K);
theorem
(((n > ( 0 ) & M1 is  symmetric) & M2 is  symmetric) implies (M1 commutes_with M2 iff ( M1 * M2 ) is  symmetric))
proof
assume that
A1: n > ( 0 )
and
A2: (M1 is  symmetric & M2 is  symmetric);
A3: (( width M1 ) = n & ( len M2 ) = n) by MATRIX_1:24;
A4: ( width M2 ) = n by MATRIX_1:24;
A5: (( M1 @ ) = M1 & ( M2 @ ) = M2) by A2,CKB28:def 1;
thus (M1 commutes_with M2 implies ( M1 * M2 ) is  symmetric)
proof
assume A6: M1 commutes_with M2;
( ( M1 * M2 ) @ ) = ( M2 * M1 ) by A1,A5,A3,A4,MATRIX_3:22
.= ( M1 * M2 ) by A6,CKB1:def 1;
hence thesis by CKB28:def 1;
end;

assume A7: ( M1 * M2 ) is  symmetric;
( M2 * M1 ) = ( ( M1 * M2 ) @ ) by A1,A5,A3,A4,MATRIX_3:22
.= ( M1 * M2 ) by A7,CKB28:def 1;
hence thesis by CKB1:def 1;
end;
